{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Mat|7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","chapter":7,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":7,"verse":1,"text":"“Do not judge, so that you won’t be judged.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":7,"verse":2,"text":"For you will be judged by the same standard with which you judge others, and you will be measured by the same measure you use.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":7,"verse":3,"text":"Why do you look at the splinter in your brother’s eye but don’t notice the beam of wood in your own eye?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":7,"verse":4,"text":"Or how can you say to your brother, ‘Let me take the splinter out of your eye,’ and look, there’s a beam of wood in your own eye?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":7,"verse":5,"text":"Hypocrite! First take the beam of wood out of your eye, and then you will see clearly to take the splinter out of your brother’s eye.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":7,"verse":6,"text":"Don’t give what is holy to dogs or toss your pearls before pigs, or they will trample them under their feet, turn, and tear you to pieces.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":7,"verse":7,"text":"“Ask, and it will be given to you. Seek, and you will find. Knock, and the door will be opened to you.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":7,"verse":8,"text":"For everyone who asks receives, and the one who seeks finds, and to the one who knocks, the door will be opened.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":7,"verse":9,"text":"Who among you, if his son asks him for bread, will give him a stone?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":7,"verse":10,"text":"Or if he asks for a fish, will give him a snake?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":7,"verse":11,"text":"If you then, who are evil, know how to give good gifts to your children, how much more will your Father in heaven give good things to those who ask him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":7,"verse":12,"text":"Therefore, whatever you want others to do for you, do also the same for them, for this is the Law and the Prophets.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":7,"verse":13,"text":"“Enter through the narrow gate. For the gate is wide and the road broad that leads to destruction, and there are many who go through it.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":7,"verse":14,"text":"How narrow is the gate and difficult the road that leads to life, and few find it.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":7,"verse":15,"text":"“Be on your guard against false prophets who come to you in sheep’s clothing but inwardly are ravaging wolves.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":7,"verse":16,"text":"You’ll recognize them by their fruit. Are grapes gathered from thornbushes or figs from thistles?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":7,"verse":17,"text":"In the same way, every good tree produces good fruit, but a bad tree produces bad fruit.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":7,"verse":18,"text":"A good tree can’t produce bad fruit; neither can a bad tree produce good fruit.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":7,"verse":19,"text":"Every tree that doesn’t produce good fruit is cut down and thrown into the fire.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":7,"verse":20,"text":"So you’ll recognize them by their fruit.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":7,"verse":21,"text":"“Not everyone who says to me, ‘Lord, Lord,’ will enter the kingdom of heaven, but only the one who does the will of my Father in heaven.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":7,"verse":22,"text":"On that day many will say to me, ‘Lord, Lord, didn’t we prophesy in your name, drive out demons in your name, and do many miracles in your name?’","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":7,"verse":23,"text":"Then I will announce to them, ‘I never knew you. Depart from me, you lawbreakers!’","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":7,"verse":24,"text":"“Therefore, everyone who hears these words of mine and acts on them will be like a wise man who built his house on the rock.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:25","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":7,"verse":25,"text":"The rain fell, the rivers rose, and the winds blew and pounded that house. Yet it didn’t collapse, because its foundation was on the rock.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:26","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":7,"verse":26,"text":"But everyone who hears these words of mine and doesn’t act on them will be like a foolish man who built his house on the sand.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:27","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":7,"verse":27,"text":"The rain fell, the rivers rose, the winds blew and pounded that house, and it collapsed. It collapsed with a great crash.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:28","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":7,"verse":28,"text":"When Jesus had finished saying these things, the crowds were astonished at his teaching,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:29","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","bookOrder":39,"chapter":7,"verse":29,"text":"because he was teaching them like one who had authority, and not like their scribes.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mat","chapter":7,"paragraphStarts":[1,7,13,15,21,24,28],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Do Not Judge"},{"beforeVerse":7,"text":"Ask, Search, Knock"},{"beforeVerse":13,"text":"Entering the Kingdom"},{"beforeVerse":24,"text":"The Two Foundations"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“Do not judge, so that you won’t be judged."},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 4:24–25","book":"Mrk","chapter":4,"verse":24,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 6:37–42","book":"Luk","chapter":6,"verse":37,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Mk 4:24–25","book":"Mrk","chapter":4,"verse":24},{"label":"Lk 6:37–42","book":"Luk","chapter":6,"verse":37}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"For you will be judged by the same standard with which you judge others, and you will be measured by the same measure you use."},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 4:24","book":"Mrk","chapter":4,"verse":24,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 6:38","book":"Luk","chapter":6,"verse":38,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 2:1","book":"Rom","chapter":2,"verse":1,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 14:10","book":"Rom","chapter":14,"verse":10,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jms 2:13","book":"Jas","chapter":2,"verse":13,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Mk 4:24","book":"Mrk","chapter":4,"verse":24},{"label":"Lk 6:38","book":"Luk","chapter":6,"verse":38},{"label":"Rm 2:1","book":"Rom","chapter":2,"verse":1},{"label":"Rm 14:10","book":"Rom","chapter":14,"verse":10},{"label":"Jms 2:13","book":"Jas","chapter":2,"verse":13}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:3","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Why do you look at the splinter in your brother’s eye but don’t notice the beam of wood in your own eye?"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 6:41","book":"Luk","chapter":6,"verse":41,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jn 8:7–9","book":"Jhn","chapter":8,"verse":7,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Lk 6:41","book":"Luk","chapter":6,"verse":41},{"label":"Jn 8:7–9","book":"Jhn","chapter":8,"verse":7}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:4","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Or how can you say to your brother, ‘Let me take the splinter out of your eye,’ and look, there’s a beam of wood in your own eye? "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:5","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Hypocrite! First take the beam of wood out of your eye, and then you will see clearly to take the splinter out of your brother’s eye. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:6","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Don’t give what is holy to dogs or toss your pearls before pigs,"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Pr 9:7–8","book":"Pro","chapter":9,"verse":7,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Pr 23:9","book":"Pro","chapter":23,"verse":9,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 15:26","book":"Mat","chapter":15,"verse":26,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" or they will trample them under their feet, turn, and tear you to pieces."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Pr 9:7–8","book":"Pro","chapter":9,"verse":7},{"label":"Pr 23:9","book":"Pro","chapter":23,"verse":9},{"label":"Mt 15:26","book":"Mat","chapter":15,"verse":26}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:7","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“Ask,"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 11:9–13","book":"Luk","chapter":11,"verse":9,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" and it will be given to you."},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 18:22","book":"Mat","chapter":18,"verse":22,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 11:24","book":"Mrk","chapter":11,"verse":24,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jn 14:13–14","book":"Jhn","chapter":14,"verse":13,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jn 15:7","book":"Jhn","chapter":15,"verse":7,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jn 16:24","book":"Jhn","chapter":16,"verse":24,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jms 1:5","book":"Jas","chapter":1,"verse":5,"letter":"g"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Jn 3:22","book":"1Jn","chapter":3,"verse":22,"letter":"h"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Jn 5:14","book":"1Jn","chapter":5,"verse":14,"letter":"i"},{"kind":"text","text":" Seek, and you will find. Knock, and the door"},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Lit and it"},{"kind":"text","text":" will be opened to you. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Lk 11:9–13","book":"Luk","chapter":11,"verse":9},{"label":"Mt 18:22","book":"Mat","chapter":18,"verse":22},{"label":"Mk 11:24","book":"Mrk","chapter":11,"verse":24},{"label":"Jn 14:13–14","book":"Jhn","chapter":14,"verse":13},{"label":"Jn 15:7","book":"Jhn","chapter":15,"verse":7},{"label":"Jn 16:24","book":"Jhn","chapter":16,"verse":24},{"label":"Jms 1:5","book":"Jas","chapter":1,"verse":5},{"label":"1Jn 3:22","book":"1Jn","chapter":3,"verse":22},{"label":"1Jn 5:14","book":"1Jn","chapter":5,"verse":14}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Lit and it"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:8","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"For everyone who asks receives, and the one who seeks finds,"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Pr 8:17","book":"Pro","chapter":8,"verse":17,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 55:6","book":"Isa","chapter":55,"verse":6,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 29:12–13","book":"Jer","chapter":29,"verse":12,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" and to the one who knocks, the door will be opened. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Pr 8:17","book":"Pro","chapter":8,"verse":17},{"label":"Is 55:6","book":"Isa","chapter":55,"verse":6},{"label":"Jr 29:12–13","book":"Jer","chapter":29,"verse":12}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:9","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Who among you, if his son asks him for bread, will give him a stone? "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:10","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Or if he asks for a fish, will give him a snake? "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:11","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"If you then, who are evil,"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 6:5","book":"Gen","chapter":6,"verse":5,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 8:21","book":"Gen","chapter":8,"verse":21,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" know how to give good gifts to your children, how much more will your Father in heaven give good things to those who ask him. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 6:5","book":"Gen","chapter":6,"verse":5},{"label":"Gn 8:21","book":"Gen","chapter":8,"verse":21}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:12","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Therefore, whatever you want others to do for you, do also the same for them, for this is the Law and the Prophets."},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 22:40","book":"Mat","chapter":22,"verse":40,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 6:31","book":"Luk","chapter":6,"verse":31,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 13:8","book":"Rom","chapter":13,"verse":8,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gl 5:14","book":"Gal","chapter":5,"verse":14,"letter":"d"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Mt 22:40","book":"Mat","chapter":22,"verse":40},{"label":"Lk 6:31","book":"Luk","chapter":6,"verse":31},{"label":"Rm 13:8","book":"Rom","chapter":13,"verse":8},{"label":"Gl 5:14","book":"Gal","chapter":5,"verse":14}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:13","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“Enter through the narrow gate."},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 13:23–24","book":"Luk","chapter":13,"verse":23,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" For the gate is wide and the road broad that leads to destruction,"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 26:8","book":"Mat","chapter":26,"verse":8,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 14:4","book":"Mrk","chapter":14,"verse":4,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jn 17:12","book":"Jhn","chapter":17,"verse":12,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 8:20","book":"Act","chapter":8,"verse":20,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 9:22","book":"Rom","chapter":9,"verse":22,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Php 1:28","book":"Php","chapter":1,"verse":28,"letter":"g"},{"kind":"text","text":" and there are many who go through it. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Lk 13:23–24","book":"Luk","chapter":13,"verse":23},{"label":"Mt 26:8","book":"Mat","chapter":26,"verse":8},{"label":"Mk 14:4","book":"Mrk","chapter":14,"verse":4},{"label":"Jn 17:12","book":"Jhn","chapter":17,"verse":12},{"label":"Ac 8:20","book":"Act","chapter":8,"verse":20},{"label":"Rm 9:22","book":"Rom","chapter":9,"verse":22},{"label":"Php 1:28","book":"Php","chapter":1,"verse":28}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:14","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"How narrow is the gate and difficult the road that leads to life, and few find it."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mat:7:15","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“Be on your guard against false prophets"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 24:11","book":"Mat","chapter":24,"verse":11,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 24:24","book":"Mat","chapter":24,"verse":24,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 13:22","book":"Mrk","chapter":13,"verse":22,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 6:26","book":"Luk","chapter":6,"verse":26,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 13:6","book":"Act","chapter":13,"verse":6,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Pt 2:1","book":"2Pe","chapter":2,"verse":1,"letter":"